                <note rend="inline" type="source">894c.20/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-23T12:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 23, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 23—5:40
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>186. Embassy’s 171, August 7, 6 p.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d723fn13">Not
                        printed.</note> The Vice Minister for Foreign Affairs today informed me that
                    the Japanese Government <pb facs="0910" n="820" xml:id="pg_820"/> disapproved of
                    the action of the Mayor of Dairen and that the Governor of the Kwantung Province
                    had taken measures to the effect that contributions from foreign firms and
                    individuals for air defense would not be exacted or expected. The Vice Minister
                    expressed his conviction that no indirect methods of pressure or retaliation for
                    failure to comply with the Mayor’s demands would be exerted. Repeated to
                    Dairen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
